text:
Trego County (standard abbreviation: TR) is a county in the U.S. state of Kansas. In 2010, 3,001 people lived there. Its county seat is WaKeeney. WaKeeney is also the biggest city in Trego County.
19th century.
In 1879, Trego County was created.
Geography.
The U.S. Census Bureau says that the county has a total area of. Of that, is land and (1.1%) is water.
Presidential elections.
Republican candidates often win Trego County. The last time a democratic candidate has won this county was in 1964.
